               <item n="m_philcomment_old">&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;a2.&lt;/b&gt; Uv.20.13d &lt;i&gt;yo ’tivākyaṃ titīkṣati&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;a3.&lt;/b&gt; Uv.20.14b &lt;i&gt;saṃrambhahetoḥ sadṛśasya caiva&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;a4.&lt;/b&gt; Uv.20.14d &lt;i&gt;tām uttamāṃ kṣāntim ihāhur āryāḥ&lt;/i&gt;. We find &lt;i&gt;ārya&lt;/i&gt; for regular &lt;i&gt;āryāḥ&lt;/i&gt;, but note that the pausa visarga is not written in this manuscript: it lacks in a5 for &lt;i&gt;mithaḥ&lt;/i&gt; (&lt;i&gt;– •&lt;/i&gt; instead), in a7 for &lt;i&gt;yuktaḥ&lt;/i&gt; (&lt;i&gt;yukta •&lt;/i&gt; instead) and in b3 for &lt;i&gt;punaḥ&lt;/i&gt; (&lt;i&gt;n· •&lt;/i&gt; instead).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;a5.&lt;/b&gt; Uv.20.15b-c &lt;i&gt;pariṣatsv atha vā mithaḥ / krodhābhibhūtaḥ puruṣaḥ&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;a5.&lt;/b&gt; The reading of this line is particularly uncertain (and changed slightly compared to [[Peyrot 2008a]]: 103), since in IOL Toch 1244 only the upper part of some akṣaras is visible, and in IOL Toch 809 only the lower. As I do not know how to restore the whole line, the number of missing syllables is uncertain; it is possible that the last &lt;i&gt;e&lt;/i&gt;-vowel of IOL Toch 1244 belongs to (the first akṣara of) &lt;i&gt;ṣemeske&lt;/i&gt; on IOL Toch 809.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;a6.&lt;/b&gt; Uv.20.16a &lt;i&gt;satyaṃ vaden na ca krudhyed&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;a7.&lt;/b&gt; Uv.20.16c &lt;i&gt;sthānair ebhis tribhir yukto&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;b1.&lt;/b&gt; Uv.20.17a-b &lt;i&gt;śāntasya hi kutaḥ krodho dāntasya samajīvinaḥ&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;b2.&lt;/b&gt; Uv.20.17d &lt;i&gt;krodho nāsti prajānataḥ&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;b2.&lt;/b&gt; traces of the &lt;i&gt;c&lt;/i&gt; and the &lt;i&gt;o&lt;/i&gt; of &lt;i&gt;ścono&lt;/i&gt; can be seen, too.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;b3.&lt;/b&gt; Uv.20.18b-c &lt;i&gt;yaḥ kruddhe krudhyate punaḥ | kruddheṣv akruddhamānas tu&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;b3.&lt;/b&gt; On IOL Toch 809, a little piece from the recto is flipped over at the left. I do not know how to restore this line either, so the number of missing akṣaras, if any, is uncertain. In [[Peyrot 2008a]]: 104 I had reconstructed a loc.sg. &lt;i&gt;(ś)c(o)n(aine)&lt;/i&gt;, which is not in accordance with the manuscript traces: what seems to be &lt;i&gt;[c]&lt;/i&gt; (the line is going slightly up) suggests rather an all.sg. &lt;i&gt;(ś)c(o)n(aiś)c(ä)&lt;/i&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;b4.&lt;/b&gt; Uv.20.18d &lt;i&gt;saṃgrāmaṃ durjayaṃ jayet&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;b5.&lt;/b&gt; Uv.20.19b &lt;i&gt;asādhuṃ sādhunā jayet&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;b6.&lt;/b&gt; Uv.20.20a &lt;i&gt;akruddhasya kutaḥ krodho&lt;/i&gt;, here apparently &lt;i&gt;akrudha(sya)&lt;/i&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</item>
